                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Document is a circular (p. 612) individually addressed to the heads of 15 departments (listed p. 613) within the Chief Secretary’s Department.</p>
               </note>Chief Secretary's Office</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne, 15. May 1886.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to request you will be good enough to forward to this Office as soon as possible, an Estimate of the probable expenditure for pensions compensations and gratuities for the financial year 1886/7. It will be convenient if the figures be arranged under the following headings viz</p>
